{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"774de276-9f97-438b-a9cf-2a9951302753","content":"Here's how to migrate your xUnit.net project to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n**1. Update packages** — replace `xunit.runner.visualstudio` with `xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform`:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Remove -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.visualstudio\" Version=\"...\" />\n\n<!-- Add -->\n<PackageReference Include=\"xunit.runner.microsoft.testing.platform\" Version=\"1.0.1\" />\n```\n\n**2. Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**3. (Optional)** Add `<UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>true</UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner>` if you want your test project to be a standalone executable.\n\n**4. Run tests** with:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nOr run the test project directly as an executable (if you enabled the runner option).\n\n**Key notes:**\n- Keep `xunit` 2.9.3 as-is — it's compatible.\n- The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property ensures `dotnet test` uses the new platform under the hood.\n- No test code changes are required.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"370a0098-37ba-4e56-a830-fd7efc64bedd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to migrate their xUnit.net project from VSTest (using xunit.runner.visualstudio) to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge of this migration.","outputTokens":386,"requestId":"BC4F:2657C1:1BB3551:1EC0B7A:69FA8FCD"},"id":"037dcb71-f360-45e8-bb78-7ede2d0c2769","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:48:23.073Z","parentId":"be0a603f-0ec9-4524-ae33-54f805150bd4"}
